snippet.textDisplay:
As someone who owned a heavily modified 5th gen Camaro.. I couldnt agree more. Ok with the front.. ok with the side profile, but If I wanted another Camaro, I'd buy a Camaro. Chevy needs to quit with the goober camaro lights in the back (in fact, many of their cars are going this way) and create something that differentiates the corvette from the rest of the line up. Or better yet, Corvette needs to pull a Genesis and be its own brand.

Would really prefer to see some form of nod to history and branding with the circle taillights.
